description._content: Description: Forest of young Cypress trees on the southern slope of Kyparissovouno. Oldest trees about 40 years, Elevation 2,800 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Aleppo Pine Forest on the northern side, Lapithos Forest, Elevation about 2,500 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
